Network trouble auto diag. Need to receive and parse logs from these devices. and then respond. Warn on administrator more precisely.

Auto backup device config, add them into git repository, showing the difference via web/client.

*nix server health check, do dns/squid first.

Add more interface, like web/GUI client, only CLI via ssh available now :(

'show sessions' shows current active telnet/ssh sessions, and someone can make request to observe others' session, when the session owner accepted, the requester can now do readonly observing, or even take charge the session, but it should be exclusive. It's too danger to operating the same vehicle in same time!
session>
	list	# replace 'show user', and TAGed each session with a short random key
	list active
	observe TAG		# observe in a window, there's cmdline below
	observe TAG take-charge	# take charge directly
	take-charge		# take charge of current observing session
	talk-to TAG		# say something to that session, receive from a TUI text block

Anyway, it faces to general network administrator, and gonna be simplify their work a lot. At least I hope so ;)
